1.What is a Gitrepository?
A Gitrepository is place that holds every file and every line of code in a Git project.

2.What are the 2 special features of a Gitrepository?
It allows you to go back to any version of your project, and lets you pull code to be used in newer versions of your code.

3.Why or how do those features help your collaborative project?
Those features help in a collaborative project because you are able to take code and files from different people and combine it into 
one. 
